27/03/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The seven East European countries invited to join NATO, including Bulgaria and Romania, signed accession protocols with the Alliance on Wednesday (26 March).
At the ceremony, the foreign ministers of Bulgaria and Romania both pledged to continue necessary reforms.
Among the priorities Bulgaria's Solomon Passy mentioned:
the fight against corruption and crime, judiciary reform and the social integration of Roma minority.
His Romanian counterpart, Mircea Geoana, said Bucharest's priorities also include anti-corruption efforts, as well as boosting administrative capacity and economic growth.
(Standart, Trud, 24 Chassa, Rompres - 27/03/03, BTA, BNT, BNR - 26/03/03)
